original: Levin, Ewert Mauritz, praktiserande läkare, Norrköping, f. 14/10/98 i Malmö av disp. Emanuel L. o. Lina Sofia Hüttner. G. 37 m. Elisabeth Enhörning. Barnr Björn f. 38, Ulla-Britt 42. — Studrex. i Malmö 19, med. kand. i Sthlm 23, med. lic. i Lund 33. Div, förordn. v. Malmö allm. sjukh. 29, e. läk. v. Lyckornas havsbad somr. 31-33, läk. där 34-38, skeppsläk. v. Johnson-linjen 34, prakt. läk. i Gbg 36-38, i Norrköp. sed. 38. Studrresa t. Amerika 34. Hobby r filateh.
translated: Levin, Ewert Mauritz, practicing physician, Norrköping, born on October 14th, 1898, in Malmö, to unmarried parents Emanuel L. and Lina Sofia Hüttner. Married in 1937 to Elisabeth Enhörning. Children: Björn, born in 1938, Ulla-Britt, born in 1942. Education: studied at Malmö University until 1919, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine degree in Stockholm in 1923, obtained a medical license in Lund in 1933. Work experience: appointed at Malmö General Hospital in 1929, employed as a doctor at Lyckornas seaside resort from summer 1931 to 1933, worked as a physician there from 1934 to 1938, served as a ship's doctor for Johnson Line in 1934, practiced medicine in Gothenburg from 1936 to 1938, and has been a practicing physician in Norrköping since 1938. Took a study trip to America in 1934. Hobbies include philately.
